Average Hourly Rate for City of Seattle Employees

This graph is designed to compare the average hourly rate and age of City of Seattle employees based on their race and enthnicity. I used position on the X axis to encode age as a quantitative variable. I also encoded average hourly rate using position on the Y axis because it is also a quantitative variable. This means users can easily see how the line change for average hourly rate as the age increases looking at the graph from left to right. I also encoded race/ethnicity using color because it is a nominal variable, so that the different races or ethnicities can be compared with each other. Now, with all the race/ethnicity values being displayed, this is difficult to read. I added an interaction, a drop down, for the user to select which race/ethnicity line they wanted to highlight. This makes it much easier for the user to compare the individual race/ethnicity with the rest of the group.
